MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/client/src/cartridges/.+\.(tsx?|jsx?)$
MATCH_CONTENT: from ['"]lucide-react['"]
ADVISORY: |
  Cartridge files must use **Phosphor Icons (Fill weight)**, not Lucide.

  The Pulse shell's locked icon contract lives in
  `apps/client/src/shells/pulse/icons.ts` — a centralized Phosphor re-export
  so future icon-library swaps are a one-file change. Lucide's 2.5px outline
  strokes look wrong next to Phosphor Fill shapes in the same shell; mixing
  them fractures weight and visual grammar, especially at small hero-badge
  sizes.

  WRONG:
      import { Crown } from 'lucide-react';
      <Crown size={20} strokeWidth={2.5} />

  RIGHT:
      import { Crown } from '../../shells/pulse/icons';
      <Crown size={20} weight="fill" color={accent} />

  If the icon you need isn't exported from `shells/pulse/icons.ts` yet, add
  it there — don't bypass the single source.
